			<item>
				<title>Code highlighting</title>
				<description>&lt;p&gt;With the new blog post, I found the need to test out pygments as part of jekyll. The code highlighting works great, but I need to seriously
consider the styling. Currently, I'm using &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/richleland/pygments-css/blob/master/default.css&quot;&gt;this&lt;/a&gt; default stylesheet from
richleland on github (thanks richleland!) and it works great but doesn't really fit in with the rest of the site.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So my list of things to do has another item on it. The work never stops.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
				<link>http://www.workmad3.com/news/2011/01/06/highlighting.html</link>
        
